
[1]revere

   REVE'RE, v.t. [L. revereor; re and vereor, to fear.]

   To regard with fear mingled with respect and affection; to venerate; to
   reverence; to honor in estimation.

   Marcus Aurelius, whom he rather revered as his father, than treated as
   his partner in the empire -
